        map.put("Debt", new ArrayList<>(Arrays.asList("Debt is an obligation that requires one party, the debtor, to pay money or other agreed-upon value to another party, the creditor. Debt is a deferred payment, or series of payments, which differentiates it from an immediate purchase. The debt may be owed by sovereign state or country, local government, company, or an individual. Commercial debt is generally subject to contractual terms regarding the amount and timing of repayments of principal and interest. Loans, bonds, notes, and mortgages are all types of debt.","Which of the following is a type of debt?", "Mortgages", "Salaries", "Car expenses", "Advertising", "A")));
